1. Định nghĩa vấn đề (Define Problem)¶

  • M t:
    • B d liu bao gm 50 mu t mi loi trong s ba loi Iris (Iris setosa, Iris virginica v Iris versicolor).
    • Bn c im c o t mi mu: chiu di v chiu rng ca cc l i(sepal) v cnh hoa (petal), tnh bng cm.
  • D liu vo:
    • sepal length (cm)
    • sepal width (cm)
    • petal length (cm)
    • petal width (cm)
  • Kt qu: class (Iris Setosa, Iris Versicolour, Iris Virginica)

(5) Mối tương quan giữa các tính chất (Correlations)¶

S tng quan (correlation) cp n mi quan h gia hai bin v cch chng c th c hoc khng cng nhau thay i.

Phng php ph bin nht tnh ton tng quan l Pearson's Correlation Coeficient, gi nh c mt phn phi chun ca cc thuc tnh lin quan. Tng quan -1 hoc 1 cho thy mi tng quan m hoc dng y tng ng. Trong khi gi tr 0 hin th khng tng quan tt c.

$$ r = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n{\left(x_i - \hat{x}\right)\left(y_i - \hat{y}\right)}}{\sqrt{\sum_{i=1}^n{\left(x_i - \hat{x}\right)^2}\sum_{i=1}^n{\left(y_i - \hat{y}\right)^2}}} $$

Mt s thut ton hc my nh hi quy tuyn tnh v logistic c hiu sut km nu c cc thuc tnh tng quan cao trong tp d liu ca bn.

Nh vy, tht s cn thit xem xt tt c cc mi tng quan theo cp ca cc thuc tnh trong tp d liu.

Box and whisker plots¶
  • https://www.simplypsychology.org/boxplots.html
  • So snh cc trung v (median) tng ng ca mi hp (box plot). Nu ng trung v ca mt hp nm bn ngoi ca mt hp so snh, th c th c s khc bit gia hai nhm.
  • So snh chiu di hp kim tra cch d liu c phn tn gia mi mu. Hp cng di th d liu cng phn tn. D liu cng nh cng t b phn tn.
  • Mt ngoi l (outlier) c nh ngha l mt im d liu nm bn ngoi phn ra (whiskers) ca hp.
  • Kim tra hng lch ca d liu (cn i, cc phn t tp trung tri, phi).
    • Median gia hp v ru (whiskers) hai bn nh nhau th phn b l i xng.
    • Median gn y hp hn v nu ru ngn hn u di ca hp, th phn phi l lch dng (lch phi).
    • Median gn u hp hn v nu ru ngn hn u trn ca hp, th phn b b lch m (lch tri).

(2) Hiển thị nhiều tính chất (Multivariate Plots) using comparison graphs¶

Scatterplots¶

What?

  • use a Cartesian coordinates system to display values of typically two variables for a set of data

Why?

  • show the relationship between two variables

Let's try an example: Showing the scatterplot between the features 'sepal_length' and 'sepal_width'

In [65]:
# pandas
df_dataset.plot.scatter('sepal-length','sepal-width');
In [66]:
# matplotlib
plt.scatter('sepal-length', 'sepal-width', data=df_dataset);
In [68]:
# seaborn
sns.scatterplot(x = df_dataset['sepal-length'], y = df_dataset['sepal-width']);
# or sns.scatter('sepal-length', 'sepal-width', data=df_dataset);
In [69]:
# With respect to the target class (species)
sns.scatterplot(x = 'sepal-length', y = 'sepal-width', hue=df_dataset['class'], data=df_dataset)
Out[69]:
<Axes: xlabel='sepal-length', ylabel='sepal-width'>

What we can conclude:

  • The iris-setosa species have smaller sepal length but higher width.
  • Versicolor lies in almost middle for length as well as width.
  • Virginica has larger sepal lengths and smaller sepal widths.

** As seen above, different tools could be used, from now on only seaborn is shown and others are lift for you to search how to do it

Out[72]:
<seaborn.axisgrid.PairGrid at 0x7fac2d1bee60>

What we can conclude:

  • Two clusters for the comparison between petal width and length.
  • Setosa has the smallest petal length as well as petal widths
  • Versicolor has average petal length and petal width
  • Virginica has the highest petal length as well as petal width.
  • Setosa has a large difference in its characteristics when compared to the other species, it has smaller petal width and length while its sepal width is high and its sepal length is low.
  • Versicolor has average dimensions whether it is sepal or petal.
  • Virginica has high petal width and length while it has small sepal width but large sepal length.
Heatmap¶

Further, we can visualise this correlation using a heatmap.

Heatmap: a two-dimensional graphical representation of data where the individual values that are contained in a matrix are represented as colors

useful to see which intersections of the categorical values, have higher concentration of the data compared to the others
